                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360613-name-264" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360613-name-264" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360613-name-264" type="surname" value="POLLARD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360613-name-264" type="given" value="STEPHEN"></interp>STEPHEN POLLARD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a shoe-maker, and live in Stafford-place South, Pimlico, and have a shop in Ormond-yard, York-street, St. James's On Saturday afternoon, the 28th of May, I was in the shop, and saw the prisoner take these boots from my door and run off—I ran after him, call<lb></lb>ing "Stop thief!"—he dropped the boots—I caught hold of him, and gave him to a policeman—I did not lose sight of him after he dropped them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> He told he Magistrate he saw a hand take them, but could not swear to me, <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> No; I said I saw him take them.</p>
